The 16-year-old boy was stabbed to death by a fellow learner at Scottsdene High School earlier this week during an altercation. CAPE TOWN - The Kraaifontein Community Policing Forum (CPF) has condemned the murder of a grade 8 pupil at a Kraaifontein school. The 16-year-old boy was stabbed to death by a fellow learner at Scottsdene High School earlier this week during an altercation. Authorities believe the incident is gang-related. The CPF s Mawethu Sila says: We got the information from police who confirmed the teenage boy was stabbed to death in a gang-related incident. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)